{{Refimprove|date=November 2015}} '''Capital punishment in the [[Bahamas]]''' is a legal punishment, and is conducted by [[hanging]] at Fox Hill Prison.<ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/593021.stm |title=AMERICAS &#124; Bahamas convict executed |publisher=BBC News |date=6 January 2000 |accessdate=8 November 2012}}</ref> The last execution in the country was on January 6, 2000.<ref name="autogenerated1"/> As of August 2012 only one convict, Mario Flowers, was under the sentence of death. Flowers' death sentence was commuted in 2016.<ref name="autogenerated2">{{cite web |url=http://www.thenassauguardian.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=33662&Itemid=27 |publisher=The Nassau Guardian |date=27 August 2012 |title=Death Row nearly empty |deadurl=no |accessdate=February 1, 2013}}</ref> Since independence from Britain, it has held more than a dozen executions.
