'''Uldarico Aguilar Alviola Sr.''' (July 4, 1883&ndash;January 1, 1966) was a Filipino [[Visayan]] novelist, one of the most important [[Cebuano language]] writers. His pseudonyms included Artagnan, Sikatuna, and M. Anabell.Also a distinguished lexicographer who made numerous claims on the origins of words,<ref name="McCoy2009">{{cite book|last=McCoy|first=Alfred W.|title=An Anarchy of Families: State and Family in the Philippines|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fawaNZu-yqUC&pg=PA338|accessdate=12 June 2013|date=January 2009|publisher=Univ of Wisconsin Press|isbn=978-0-299-22984-9|page=338}}</ref> he was the editor of ''[[Ang Suga Magazine in Cebu Normal University]]'', and several other Spanish language publications.<ref name="Lifshey2012">{{cite book|last=Lifshey|first=Adam|title=The Magellan Fallacy: Globalization and the Emergence of Asian and African Literature in Spanish|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vVu84ugeK1MC&pg=PA138|accessdate=12 June 2013|date=14 September 2012|publisher=University of Michigan Press|isbn=978-0-472-11847-2|page=138}}</ref>
In 1962 he received the [[LUDABI]] award for his contributions to [[Cebuano people|Cebuano]] culture. He was also once a Deputy Governor of [[Cebu Province|Cebu]], one of the [[provinces]] of the [[Philippines]].<ref name="AcostaCouncil1977">{{cite book|last=Acosta|first=Emma Montecillo|title=A subject guide to the ordinances enacted by the City Council of Cebu, 1945-1975|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nzHVAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=12 June 2013|year=1977|publisher=Cebu City Council, University of San Carlos}}</ref>
==Books== *''Felicitas'', 1912 *''Ang Gugma sa Lalaki'', 1921 *''Ang Gugma sa Babaye'', 1918 *''Gumaran sa Kinabuhi'', 1934
